{"id": "duc04-testb-1:0#2", "contents": "The players are taking steps to win public opinion, holding make-shift press conferences in 11 cities throughout the country on Monday. Patrick Ewing, the union president, and several teammates will speak at SUNY-Purchase in Purchase, N.Y., where the Knicks train during the season. The message from the players is clear: if the owners would call an end to the lockout, they would be ready to play today. About 100 players are expected to attend, speak and sign autographs for fans afterward. The players' actions are seen as a way to show their commitment to playing and to pressure the owners to negotiate a deal."}
